A MAN suspected of murdering a Khayelitsha woman in her home and then dumping her body in a public toilet is expected to appear in court tomorrow, Western Cape police said.Her body was found in the toilet in RR Block in the informal settlement at 8am on Monday, Captain Frederick van Wyk said today.She was believed to have been murdered in her home in Site C, Khayelitsha. Van Wyk did not provide the woman&rsquo;s name.A suspect, 27, was arrested yesterday afternoon. He would appear in the Khayelitsha Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Thursday on a murder charge.Another young Khayelitsha woman was found murdered on Sunday. Noluvo Swelindawo (22) was found shot dead on a footbridge near the Driftsands Nature Reserve. It was suspected that she was killed because she was lesbian.On 2 March this year, 19-year-old Sinoxolo Mafevuka was found naked and strangled in a communal toilet in SST Block, Town Two, Khayelitsha. Her boyfriend&rsquo;s two cousins were arrested for the crime. They are awaiting trial on charges of rape and murder.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/another-khayelitsha-woman-murdered-dumped-in-communal-toilet-20161207